'''Stephen John Dawson''' (born 4 December 1985) is an Irish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as for English club [[Rochdale A.F.C.|Rochdale]].

He primarily plays as a [[Midfielder#Centre midfielder|central midfielder]], although he has also been deployed in [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|defensive midfield]], he is noted for his aggressive and highly competitive style of play.

In his 12-year-long playing career, Dawson began his career with English club [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]], where he failed to make his debut. He instead made his debut for [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]] where he would spend most of his career, and with whom he signed in 2005, going on to appear in 114 official games. Apart from Mansfield Town, Dawson has previously played for [[Bury F.C.|Bury]], [[Leyton Orient F.C.|Leyton Orient]], and [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]]. In 2014, he signed for Rochdale. Despite suffering with some injuries during his time at [[Spotland Stadium|Spotland]], Dawson has established himself as a regular part of the first team.

On the international level, Dawson has represented the [[Republic of Ireland national football team]] at Under-21 level on two occasions.<ref name="Under 21<U+2013>2005/2006 Squad Profile">{{cite web|url=http://www.fai.ie/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=58&Itemid=9|title=Under 21<U+2013>2005/2006 Squad Profile |date=20 March 2006|publisher=Football Association of Ireland|accessdate=29 April 2008}}</ref>

==Early career==
Born in [[Dublin]], Dawson began his professional football career as a trainee at [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]]<ref name="sbase">{{cite web|url=http://www.soccerbase.com/players_details.sd?playerid=40420|title=Stephen Dawson  |work=Soccerbase|publisher=[[Racing Post]]|accessdate=29 April 2008}}</ref> having joined from Dublin schoolboy team Portmarnock AFC having spent 7 years before that with St Malachys Fc and although he became a regular in the reserve side, he did not graduate to the first team and rejected an offer of a new contract on reduced terms in May 2005.<ref name="BBC170505">{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/l/leicester_city/4555711.stm|title=Dawson snubs Foxes contract offer |date=17 May 2005|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=29 April 2008}}</ref>

==Club career==

===Mansfield Town===
He joined [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]] in the summer of 2005<ref name="BBC100807">{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/m/mansfield_town/6940141.stm|title=Dawson signs new Mansfield deal |date=10 August 2007|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=29 April 2008}}</ref> and scored on his debut against [[Stockport County F.C.|Stockport]] in August 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soccerbase.com/players_details.sd?playerid=40420&seasonid=135|title=Games played by Stephen Dawson in 2005/2006|work=Soccerbase|publisher=Racing Post|accessdate=29 April 2008}}</ref> He signed a new one-year contract in August 2007<ref name="BBC100807" /> and by the end of the 2007<U+2013>08 season, had made over 125 appearances in all competitions for Mansfield Town.<ref name=sbase />

===Bury===
[[File:Stephen Dawson 2.jpg|thumb|Dawson playing for [[Bury F.C.|Bury]]]]
After Mansfield Town were relegated to the [[Football Conference]] at the end of the 2007<U+2013>08 season, he was out of contract<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/m/mansfield_town/7405428.stm|title=Seven players to leave Mansfield |date=16 May 2008|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=17 May 2008}}</ref> and joined [[Bury F.C.|Bury]] on a two-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/bury/7481432.stm|title= Midfielder Dawson commits to Bury|date=30 June 2008|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=3 July 2008}}</ref> Dawson made his [[Bury F.C.|Bury]] debut on 9 August 2008 on the opening day of the season with a 1<U+2013>0 win over [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]] at Gigg Lane. Dawson got his first goal for Bury on 18 October 2008 in a 3<U+2013>1 win at [[Dagenham & Redbridge F.C.|Dagenham & Redbridge]].

===Leyton Orient===
On 4 June 2010 he signed for [[Football League One|League One]] side [[Leyton Orient F.C.|Leyton Orient]]. He then became Leyton Orient's Captain. Dawson scored his first goal for the O's in their 2<U+2013>1 win against Tranmere Rovers on 11 December 2010.

===Barnsley===
On 31 January 2012 he signed for Championship side Barnsley for an undisclosed fee. Despite suffering with injuries during his time at Oakwell, Dawson established himself as a regular part of the first team.
He was involved in an angry confrontation with Barnsley supporters after the team's 5<U+2013>0 defeat at [[Huddersfield Town F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] in March 2014, for which he apologised and made a small financial donation to Barnsley Hospice.<ref>{{cite news|title=Dawson apologises|url=http://www.barnsleyfc.co.uk/news/article/stephen-dawson-apologises-to-supporters-1394604.aspx}}</ref>

Just a month later, Dawson was named as one of seven footballers arrested in connection with alleged [[spot-fixing]] of football matches. When asked Dawson said "They came at 6.30am. Ten officers. They searched our house from top to bottom and seized some of our belongings&nbsp;<U+2013> my mobile phones, my laptop, my girlfriend<U+2019>s phone, documents. Then they said I had to go down to the station. We didn't know what was going on." "It nearly broke me," Dawson said, three days after the National Crime Agency ended his nine-month ordeal by confirming that the case against him has been dropped.<ref>{{cite news|title=Dawson named in spot fixing arrests|url=http://www.barnsley-chronicle.co.uk/sport/article/7741/dawson-named-in-spot-fixing-scandal}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rochdaleafc.co.uk/news/article/a-statement-from-stephen-dawson-2213112.aspx|title=A Statement From Stephen Dawson|work=rochdaleafc.co.uk}}</ref>

===Rochdale===
[[File:Stephen Dawson 6.jpg|thumb|upright|Dawson playing for [[Rochdale A.F.C.|Rochdale]]]]
On 13 August 2014, Dawson signed for [[Rochdale A.F.C.|Rochdale]] on a one-year contact.<ref>{{cite news|title=Stephen Dawson Joins Rochdale |url=http://www.rochdaleafc.co.uk/news/article/dawson-signs-1822710.aspx|publisher=[[Rochdale A.F.C.]]|accessdate=13 August 2014}}</ref>

==International career==
He has also represented the [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]] at Under-21 level twice.<ref name="Under 21<U+2013>2005/2006 Squad Profile"/>

==Personal life==
His younger brother [[Kevin Dawson (footballer, born 1990)|Kevin]] plays for fellow League One side [[Yeovil Town F.C.|Yeovil Town]].{{citation needed|date=September 2014}}

